==English==
===Idiom===
'''[[don't]] [[cry]] over [[spilt]] [[milk]]'''
# {{idiom}} It is no use worrying about things that cannot be [[rectified]].

===Synonyms===
*[[spilt milk]]
*[[no use crying over spilt milk]]

===Translations===
{{top}}
*Chinese: [[覆水難收]], [[覆水难收]]
*Finnish: Ei kannata itkeä kaatunutta maitoa
{{mid}}
*Japanese: [[覆水盆に返らず]] (fukusui bon ni kaerazu)
{{bottom}}
*Russian: [[Снявши голову, по волосам не плачут]],[[После драки кулаками не машут]]
*Swedish: Gråt inte över spilld mjölk
*French : Il ne faut pas pleurer sur le lait renversé. The origin may be found in a fable by [[w:Jean de La Fontaine|Jean de La Fontaine]], ''la laitière et le pot au lait'' (the milkmaid and the milkpot) ; but the poet borrowed themes from [[w:Aesop|Aesop]].
*Portuguese: Não chore sobre o leite derramado

